org.globalplatform.broker

Interface CDCVMBrokerListener

  • All Superinterfaces:
    BrokerListener, javacard.framework.Shareable

    public interface CDCVMBrokerListener
extends BrokerListener
    Extension of the BrokerListener interface including definitions specific to the CDCVM (Consumer Device CVM) use case.

    When invoking this interface, in order to form a valid parameter value the caller shall:

    • For BrokerListener.onBrokerEvent(short, short, short, short, short, short, short, short, short):
      • For the context parameter, build a short value of the form '00XX' where:
        • XX is encoded as follows:
          • Bits b1 and b2 encode the CDCVM session identifier (if any) to which the notified event belongs (i.e. within session) or relates (i.e. start or end of session). Values 1, 2, and 3 are valid CDCVM session identifiers and consecutive notifications indicating the same session identifier shall be interpreted by the notified Application as pertaining to the same session.
            A value of 0 shall be used to indicate that the notified event is independent and does not pertain to any CDCVM session.
          • Bits b3 to b8 are RFU.
      • For the object parameter, any of OBJECT_CDCVM_XXX constants.
      • For the attributes parameter, build a short value of the form '00XY' where:
        • X encodes the CDCVM try limit (from 1 to 15). A value of 0 shall be used to indicate that the try limit is unknown, not applicable or greater than 15.
        • Y encodes the CDCVM remaining tries (from 1 to 14). A value of 0 shall be used to indicate that the CDCVM is blocked (NOTE: this information shall not conflict with the value provided for the event parameter). A value of 15 ('F') indicates that the number of remaining tries is unknown, not applicable or greater than 14.
      • For the event parameter, any of EVENT_CDCVM_XXX constants.
      • For the environment parameter, combine (OR-ing) a ENV_CAPTURE_XXX constant with a ENV_VERIFICATION_XXX constant.
      • For the assurance parameter: use the ASSURANCE_CDCVM_UNKNOWN constant (NOTE: other choices may be defined in the future).
      • For the security parameter, combine (OR-ing) a SECURITY_CDCVM_C2V_XXX constant with a SECURITY_CDCVM_V2B_XXX constant.
      • For the device parameter, combine (OR-ing) a DEVICE_CDCVM_CAPTURE_XXX constant with a DEVICE_CDCVM_VERIFICATION_XXX constant.

    E.g. 

       listener.onBrokerEvent((short)0x0000, // context
                          OBJECT_CDCVM_BIO_FINGER_DEFAULT, // object
                          (short)0x0033, // attributes
                          EVENT_CDCVM_EVENT_VERIFICATION_SUCCEEDED,
                          ...);
    The implementation of this interface may use the MASK_XXX constants to inspect the received parameters. E.g.

       short session = (short)(context&MASK_CONTEXT_CDCVM_SESSION);

   short object_type = (short)(object&MASK_OBJECT_CDCVM_TYPE);

   switch (object_type) {
   case CDCVM_TYPE_PASSCODE:
     ...
     break;

   case CDCVM_TYPE_BIO_FINGER:
     ...
     break;
   }
    Since:
    • export file version 1.0: initial version.
    • export file version 1.1: new constant EVENT_CDCVM_EVENT_NOT_ENROLLED

      • SIO_CDCVM_BROKER_LISTENER

        static final byte SIO_CDCVM_BROKER_LISTENER
        Constant used to retrieve an implementation of this interface from an Application (0xB1).

        When using this constant to retrieve a BrokerListener instance, the caller should explicitly cast the object returned by the Application to the type CDCVMBrokerListener to ensure it is of the correct type.

      • EVENT_CDCVM_EVENT_VERIFICATION_INVALIDATED

        static final short EVENT_CDCVM_EVENT_VERIFICATION_INVALIDATED
        Event indicating that any previously recorded occurrence of EVENT_CDCVM_EVENT_VERIFICATION_SUCCEEDED shall be discarded. Based on the value of the object parameter, this requirement would apply to a specific CDCVM object or all CDCVM objects (known to the Application).

        The Broker Application is only required to notify this event once for any particular CDCVM object. Once this event's been notified, until it becomes aware of a new CDCVM event, the Broker Application shall notify EVENT_CDCVM_EVENT_NOT_PERFORMED when being requested about the last CDCVM event pertaining to the same CDCVM object.

        See Also:
